      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(?i)(pubnub_subscribe_key|subscribe_key|pubnub_sub_key|sub_key|pubnub_subscription_key|subscription_key)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\"']?(sub-c-[a-f0-9]{8}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{12})[\"']?",
        "message": "PubNub Subscription Key detected in variable assignment. PubNub is a real-time messaging platform. Subscription keys enable access to channels, message streams, presence information, and historical data. While these keys are typically used client-side, exposing them in version control creates security risks including unauthorized channel access, message monitoring, quota exhaustion, and presence tracking. Use PubNub Access Manager (PAM) to grant granular, time-limited permissions. Rotate this key immediately from your PubNub Admin Portal, implement environment-based configuration, and avoid hardcoding keys in source code. For production applications, use server-side authentication with PAM tokens.",
